minikube start : start cluster
kubectl cluster-info : get infos + link for access
kubectl get nodes : get nodes with status


kubectl create deployment <name> --image=<image> : create a deployment for app
kubectl get deployments

kubectl proxy
kubectl get pods
http://localhost:8001/api/v1/namespaces/default/pods/$POD_NAME/

kubectl get - list resources
kubectl describe - show detailed information about a resource
kubectl logs - print the logs from a container in a pod
kubectl exec - execute a command on a container in a pod
 kubectl exec POD_NAME -- COMMAND


kubectl expose deployment/kubernetes-bootcamp --type="NodePort" --port 8080
 Voir section Using a service to expose your app


Scaling
kubectl scale deployments/kubernetes-bootcamp --replicas=4

Update
kubectl set image deployments/kubernetes-bootcamp kubernetes-bootcamp=jocatalin/kubernetes-bootcamp:v2
Confirm update
kubectl rollout status deployments/kubernetes-bootcamp
Rollback
kubectl rollout undo deployments/kubernetes-bootcamp



Surement utile:
https://kubernetes.io/docs/tasks/run-application/horizontal-pod-autoscale/

